description:
Read this epic, cosmic adventure of the God of Thunder! Of all writers, who ever told of Marvel's Prince of Asgard, has no one left such an awe-inspiring work as Walter Simonson. In this Volume you find the first issues of his spectacular era, which would redefine the world of Thor.

Collects The Mighty Thor #337-343

Two reporters with the names Lois & Clark appear in this comics and also other references to Superman are made.
name: Vol. 4 - Thor - Der letzte Wikinger

description: The all-new, two-fisted pulp adventures Terrific Twosome of Toronto! This issue: “Rhyme Spree pt 1 of 2” That pernicious pirate of the pen, The Poet, has the city in the thrall of a romantic rhapsody with a crime campaign based in villainous verse. Can the Red Panda and the Flying Squirrel deduce his mysterious motives in time? Plus two more serialized chapters of the prose pulp novel “Pyramid of Peril”, and a behind the scenes “agent file” on mild-mannered reporter Jack Peters.
name: Rhyme Spree Part 1 of 2

deck: A bold new direction for the Teen Titans
description:
Red Robin, Wonder Girl, Raven, Bunker and Beast Boy step out of the shadows of the adult heroes of the DC Universe to offer bold, exciting and sometime dangerous ideas on how to protect a world full of superpowered teenagers – any one of whom could be the next heroic figure or major villain!

Note: Batman only appears on the Batman variant cover.
